      <div class="msgContentFrame">Heres my theory for a really good tank build from looking at the abilities on offer from each class. This build will take a ridiculous amount of time to acquire :P. <br /> <br />STATS <br />STR and DEX to 40 then focus mainly on VIT and MND for healing potency and mp <br /> <br /> <br />ABILITES <br />Pulgist - rank 40 for Taunt II (rank 10 for the first version) <br />Marauder - rank 48 for Defender II (rank 10 for the first version) <br />Conjurer - rank 48 for Cure III (rank 4 for Cure and 20 for Cure II) <br />GLADIATOR - rank 50 for all that lovely tank ness  <br /> <br />So the idea of it is to use the two taunts to draw enemies attention then use the cures (aoe for more hate) to keep yourself alive and draw more aggro. <br /> <br />Ive had someone tell me that a tank should focus on DEX as their secondary stat for evasion, i know that not putting alot into dex would mean you would take more damage but having the points in MND would mean that you could make up for it with cures which would also draw more aggro. <br /> <br />let me know what you guys think or if im missing something and it wouldn't work. I am currently levelling the classes to get the first versions and cure II then im gonna hit up that gladiator goodness :D, i was gonna playing lancer and was gonna be a DPS char but I got sick of the lack of tanks and the aggro getting thrown around in parties.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=4454266" title="http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=4454266" rel="external nofollow">http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=4454266</a> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1812910.png" height="144" width="482" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
