      <div class="msgContentFrame">To be clear, the issue with a gladiator trying to hold threat with Cure is that you're not going to be able to heal yourself through any kind of challenging encounter.  If you could, Gladiator would be a broken class slated for a nerf.  That means you're going to have other classes curing you even if you're curing yourself, and they're going to build more threat than you because their cures are going to be bigger and they're going to be curing multiple players.  It's a pretty safe bet that when you factor in the cast time on those cures, you'd be better off doing something else to generate the same (or higher) enmity. <br /> <br />Also, STR and DEX to 40 is...umm...very low.  At physical level 40 my STR, VIT, and DEX are all well above 70 and my INT, MND, and PIE are all at or above 40.  By physical level 50 I'll have some stats near, at, or above 100. <br /> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 17th 2010  6:57pm by Aurelius </span></i></div>
