      <div class="msgContentFrame">I can see cure being used to tank as a GLA. All you need to do is take a look at PLD in FFXI. I played PLD/WAR to 75 and Cure was one of the best hate pulling spells affter Flash. You got to stop and think. You don't need to out cure the healers to have cure help you keep hate. A cure or 2 along with a taunt and provoke can realy make keeping hate an easy job.  <br /> <br /> I have started using cure on my GLA and find that it plays alot like the FFXI PLD. I start off with provoke swich over to a cure after 3 hits then pop off Taunt after a few more hits. Doing this alone seems to be all I need to keep hate for most fights. Its not that cure helps keep you alive. Cure pulls a lot of hate much more than a high dmg attack or spell. As for geting hit stoping you from casting.. I have been in quite a few fights where I am tanking 2 or 3 mobs at one time and still get cure off. Just lastnight I was in a hippogrif group just lastnight tanking 2 at a time and geting cure off no problem. <br /> <br /> I am just trying to say don't write cure off so fast. I have found that with cure the GLA plays a lot like the PLD. Now all this could change as we get closer to 50. but for now Cure will keep a place on my skill setup.</div>
