      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">F3rth wrote:</div><div class="orig"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Kashius wrote:</div><div class="orig">Why wouldn't Phalanx be your primary hate building tool over Voke/Taunt? Just wondering... <br /> <br />-Kash</div></div> <br /> <br />Not to mention heavy slash and heavy stab. Way better at gaining enmity than provoke is. <br /> <br />Also while we're fantasizing, fast cast trait from conjurer (8k guild marks, optimal rank 30) and Intimidation(increased enmity from every action) trait from marauder (also 8k marks and optimal rank 30.) as well as disorient(gains enmity and lowers mob evasion, when it lands) from marauder... <br /> <br />Also I would advise against leaving dexterity gimped... Gladiators already have a horrible time hitting things, and most of our tools to get hate (phalanx, and heavy slash) are semi dependent on our ability to hit accurately.</div></div> <br /> <br /> <br />Add prime conditionning (pug20 + 8k mark) to get healed from each healing, inceasing your suvivability with lower tier cure, arguably less enmity generating. <br />And fleet of foot for kitting, if ever kitting is a viable strategy. thats all jobs except archer to 20 :)</div>
